### Test Call System

### 1. Create a new call
POST http://localhost:3001/api/calls
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_HERE
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "requesterId": "REQUESTER_ID_HERE",
  "helperId": "HELPER_ID_HERE",
  "callId": "TWILIO_CALL_ID_HERE"
}

### 2. Disconnect a call
POST http://localhost:3001/api/calls/CALL_ID_HERE/disconnect
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_HERE

### 3. Get active calls for current user
GET http://localhost:3001/api/calls/active
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_HERE

### 4. Get call history for current user
GET http://localhost:3001/api/calls/history?limit=10&offset=0
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_HERE

### 5. Test call flow:
### Step 1: Create helper request
POST http://localhost:3001/api/helper/request
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_HERE
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "requesterId": "REQUESTER_ID_HERE",
  "requesterName": "Test User",
  "helperIds": ["HELPER_ID_HERE"]
}

### Step 2: Helper accepts request
POST http://localhost:3001/api/helper/respond
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_HERE
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "requestId": "REQUEST_ID_HERE",
  "helperId": "HELPER_ID_HERE",
  "response": "accepted"
}

### Step 3: Create call (after helper accepts)
POST http://localhost:3001/api/calls
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_HERE
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "requesterId": "REQUESTER_ID_HERE",
  "helperId": "HELPER_ID_HERE",
  "callId": "TWILIO_CALL_ID_HERE"
}

### Step 4: Disconnect call (either user can disconnect)
POST http://localhost:3001/api/calls/CALL_ID_HERE/disconnect
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_HERE
